05/02/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A national procession through the capital with be held on Friday (February 9th) evening, to mark eight years of imprisonment for the five Bulgarian nurses held in Libya.
The event is being organised by the private national TV channel bTV, Darik Radio and Standart newspaper, which are behind an international campaign on behalf of the nurses dubbed "You Are Not Alone".
The procession will begin with a prayer for them at the St Alexander Nevski cathedral, will pass through downtown Sofia and will end with a concert at the central St Alexander Nevski square.
The nurses and a Palestinian doctor have been sentenced to death for allegedly infecting hundreds of children with HIV, despite expert testimony to the contrary.
(Standart - 05/02/07)
